wikipedia_page.main: William Henry "Fatty" Foulke (12 April 1874 – 1 May 1916; sometimes spelled Foulk, Foulkes) was an English professional cricketer and football player. Foulke was renowned for his great size (6 ft 9 in (2.06 m) by some estimates) and weight, reaching perhaps 24 stones (152 kg; 336 lb) at the end of his career, although reports on his weight vary.
